    "recap_headline": "University of Louisiana at Lafayette Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SAN MARCOS, Texas \u2013\nRashawn Galloway slugged a pair of three-run homers and Manny Salas added a two-run blast as Texas State secured the Sun Belt Conference series win over No. 25-ranked Louisiana with an 11-4 victory Saturday afternoon at Bobcat Ballpark.\nGalloway's first homer, a line drive that cleared the left-field fence, erased an early 3-0 lead by the Cajuns (16-7, 2-3 SBC). His second, a towering drive to left-center, put the Bobcats (14-8, 2-3 SBC) ahead 6-3.\nBoth homers came with two outs off Cajuns starter\nAndrew Herrmann\n(3-1). Herrmann suffered his first loss of the season after allowing seven runs in five innings \u2013 four were unearned. He walked two and struck out five.\nSalas' home run came off reliever\nGarret Carter\nas part of a four-run, seventh inning in which Texas State sent eight men to the plate and collected five hits.\nLouisiana jumped out to a quick start against Bobcats starter Sam Hall, scoring in the first inning on an RBI single by\nRigoberto Hernandez\n. The Cajuns extended the lead to 3-0 in the third when\nDrew Markle\nhit a two-run homer \u2014 his third of the season \u2014 after\nDonovan LaSalle\nreached on an error.\nTexas State answered in the third after an error on a ground ball gave the Bobcats a leadoff runner. Austin Mungia singled with one out, and after Herrmann struck out Jackson Cotton for the second out, Galloway's liner just cleared the fence in left field to tie the game.\nThe Cajuns regained the lead in the fifth inning when\nLee Amedee\nsingled against the Texas State shift and later scored when\nColt Brown's\nsacrifice fly was dropped for an error in right-center.\nBut after recording the first two outs in the bottom of the fifth, Herrmann allowed a double to Mungia and walked Cotton to set up Galloway, who delivered his second three-run homer of the game to give Texas State the lead for good.\nReliever Cade Smith (1-0) was sharp out of the bullpen for the Bobcats, allowing just two hits over 4.2 scoreless innings. He did not issue a walk and struck out seven to earn the win.\nGalloway led Texas State's 12-hit attack with three hits, while Ethan Farris and Mungia added two hits apiece.\nAmedee and Hernandez each collected two hits for the Cajuns, who finished with nine hits.\nLouisiana will try to avoid the sweep Sunday at 1 p.m. in the final game of the series in San Marcos.\nFans are encouraged to stay engaged with the Ragin' Cajuns by downloading the #GeauxCajuns app. Click\nhere\nfor iOS/Apple platforms and\nhere\nfor Android platforms.\nFor the latest updates on Ragin' Cajuns baseball, follow on Facebook (RaginCajunsBaseball), Twitter (@RaginCajunsBSB) and Instagram (@RaginCajunsBSB) or check RaginCajuns.com.",
    "watch_url": "https://www.espn.com/watch/player/_/id/6ee6721a-06b2-4bea-b021-56db3a784215"
